51const char kInline[] = "inline:";

53void GetSupportedSdesCryptoSuiteNames(
54 void (*func)(const webrtc::CryptoOptions&, std::vector<int>*),
55 const webrtc::CryptoOptions& crypto_options,
56 std::vector<std::string>* names) {
57 std::vector<int> crypto_suites;
58 func(crypto_options, &crypto_suites);
59 for (const auto crypto : crypto_suites) {
60 names->push_back(rtc::SrtpCryptoSuiteToName(crypto));
61 }
62}
63
64webrtc::RtpExtension RtpExtensionFromCapability(
65 const webrtc::RtpHeaderExtensionCapability& capability) {
66 return webrtc::RtpExtension(capability.uri,
67 capability.preferred_id.value_or(1));
68}
69
70cricket::RtpHeaderExtensions RtpHeaderExtensionsFromCapabilities(
71 const std::vector<webrtc::RtpHeaderExtensionCapability>& capabilities) {
72 cricket::RtpHeaderExtensions exts;
73 for (const auto& capability : capabilities) {
74 exts.push_back(RtpExtensionFromCapability(capability));
75 }
76 return exts;
77}
78
79std::vector<webrtc::RtpHeaderExtensionCapability>
80UnstoppedRtpHeaderExtensionCapabilities(
81 std::vector<webrtc::RtpHeaderExtensionCapability> capabilities) {
82 capabilities.erase(
83 std::remove_if(
84 capabilities.begin(), capabilities.end(),
85 [](const webrtc::RtpHeaderExtensionCapability& capability) {
86 return capability.direction == RtpTransceiverDirection::kStopped;
87 }),
88 capabilities.end());
89 return capabilities;
90}
91
92bool IsCapabilityPresent(const webrtc::RtpHeaderExtensionCapability& capability,
93 const cricket::RtpHeaderExtensions& extensions) {
94 return std::find_if(extensions.begin(), extensions.end(),
95 [&capability](const webrtc::RtpExtension& extension) {
96 return capability.uri == extension.uri;
97 }) != extensions.end();
98}
99
100cricket::RtpHeaderExtensions UnstoppedOrPresentRtpHeaderExtensions(
101 const std::vector<webrtc::RtpHeaderExtensionCapability>& capabilities,
102 const cricket::RtpHeaderExtensions& unencrypted,
103 const cricket::RtpHeaderExtensions& encrypted) {
104 cricket::RtpHeaderExtensions extensions;
105 for (const auto& capability : capabilities) {
106 if (capability.direction != RtpTransceiverDirection::kStopped ||
107 IsCapabilityPresent(capability, unencrypted) ||
108 IsCapabilityPresent(capability, encrypted)) {
109 extensions.push_back(RtpExtensionFromCapability(capability));
110 }
111 }
112 return extensions;
113}

120// http://www.iana.org/assignments/rtp-parameters/rtp-parameters.xml
121// RFC4585

123// RFC5124
124const char kMediaProtocolDtlsSavpf[] = "UDP/TLS/RTP/SAVPF";

126// We always generate offers with "UDP/TLS/RTP/SAVPF" when using DTLS-SRTP,
127// but we tolerate "RTP/SAVPF" in offers we receive, for compatibility.
128const char kMediaProtocolSavpf[] = "RTP/SAVPF";

130// Note that the below functions support some protocol strings purely for
131// legacy compatibility, as required by JSEP in Section 5.1.2, Profile Names
132// and Interoperability.
133
134static bool IsDtlsRtp(const std::string& protocol) {
135 // Most-likely values first.
136 return protocol == "UDP/TLS/RTP/SAVPF" || protocol == "TCP/TLS/RTP/SAVPF" ||
137 protocol == "UDP/TLS/RTP/SAVP" || protocol == "TCP/TLS/RTP/SAVP";
138}
139
140static bool IsPlainRtp(const std::string& protocol) {
141 // Most-likely values first.
142 return protocol == "RTP/SAVPF" || protocol == "RTP/AVPF" ||
143 protocol == "RTP/SAVP" || protocol == "RTP/AVP";
144}
145
146static RtpTransceiverDirection NegotiateRtpTransceiverDirection(
147 RtpTransceiverDirection offer,
148 RtpTransceiverDirection wants) {
149 bool offer_send = webrtc::RtpTransceiverDirectionHasSend(offer);
150 bool offer_recv = webrtc::RtpTransceiverDirectionHasRecv(offer);
151 bool wants_send = webrtc::RtpTransceiverDirectionHasSend(wants);
152 bool wants_recv = webrtc::RtpTransceiverDirectionHasRecv(wants);
153 return webrtc::RtpTransceiverDirectionFromSendRecv(offer_recv && wants_send,
154 offer_send && wants_recv);
155}

164
165static bool CreateCryptoParams(int tag,
166 const std::string& cipher,
167 CryptoParams* crypto_out) {
168 int key_len;
169 int salt_len;
170 if (!rtc::GetSrtpKeyAndSaltLengths(rtc::SrtpCryptoSuiteFromName(cipher),
171 &key_len, &salt_len)) {
172 return false;
173 }
174
175 int master_key_len = key_len + salt_len;
176 std::string master_key;
177 if (!rtc::CreateRandomData(master_key_len, &master_key)) {
178 return false;
179 }
180
181 RTC_CHECK_EQ(master_key_len, master_key.size());
182 std::string key = rtc::Base64::Encode(master_key);
183
184 crypto_out->tag = tag;
185 crypto_out->cipher_suite = cipher;
186 crypto_out->key_params = kInline;
187 crypto_out->key_params += key;
188 return true;
189}
190
191static bool AddCryptoParams(const std::string& cipher_suite,
192 CryptoParamsVec* cryptos_out) {
193 int size = static_cast<int>(cryptos_out->size());
194
195 cryptos_out->resize(size + 1);
196 return CreateCryptoParams(size, cipher_suite, &cryptos_out->at(size));
197}

199void AddMediaCryptos(const CryptoParamsVec& cryptos,
200 MediaContentDescription* media) {
201 for (const CryptoParams& crypto : cryptos) {
202 media->AddCrypto(crypto);
203 }
204}
205
206bool CreateMediaCryptos(const std::vector<std::string>& crypto_suites,
207 MediaContentDescription* media) {
208 CryptoParamsVec cryptos;
209 for (const std::string& crypto_suite : crypto_suites) {
210 if (!AddCryptoParams(crypto_suite, &cryptos)) {
211 return false;
212 }
213 }
214 AddMediaCryptos(cryptos, media);
215 return true;
216}

225bool FindMatchingCrypto(const CryptoParamsVec& cryptos,
226 const CryptoParams& crypto,
227 CryptoParams* crypto_out) {
228 auto it = absl::c_find_if(
229 cryptos, [&crypto](const CryptoParams& c) { return crypto.Matches(c); });
230 if (it == cryptos.end()) {
231 return false;
232 }
233 *crypto_out = *it;
234 return true;
235}

237// For audio, HMAC 32 (if enabled) is prefered over HMAC 80 because of the
238// low overhead.
239void GetSupportedAudioSdesCryptoSuites(
240 const webrtc::CryptoOptions& crypto_options,
241 std::vector<int>* crypto_suites) {
242 if (crypto_options.srtp.enable_aes128_sha1_32_crypto_cipher) {
243 crypto_suites->push_back(rtc::SRTP_AES128_CM_SHA1_32);
244 }
245 crypto_suites->push_back(rtc::SRTP_AES128_CM_SHA1_80);
246 if (crypto_options.srtp.enable_gcm_crypto_suites) {
247 crypto_suites->push_back(rtc::SRTP_AEAD_AES_256_GCM);
248 crypto_suites->push_back(rtc::SRTP_AEAD_AES_128_GCM);
249 }
250}
251

253 const webrtc::CryptoOptions& crypto_options,
254 std::vector<std::string>* crypto_suite_names) {
255 GetSupportedSdesCryptoSuiteNames(GetSupportedAudioSdesCryptoSuites,
256 crypto_options, crypto_suite_names);
257}

293// Support any GCM cipher (if enabled through options). For video support only
294// 80-bit SHA1 HMAC. For audio 32-bit HMAC is tolerated (if enabled) unless
295// bundle is enabled because it is low overhead.
296// Pick the crypto in the list that is supported.
297static bool SelectCrypto(const MediaContentDescription* offer,
298 bool bundle,
299 const webrtc::CryptoOptions& crypto_options,
300 CryptoParams* crypto_out) {
301 bool audio = offer->type() == MEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO;
302 const CryptoParamsVec& cryptos = offer->cryptos();
303
304 for (const CryptoParams& crypto : cryptos) {
305 if ((crypto_options.srtp.enable_gcm_crypto_suites &&
306 rtc::IsGcmCryptoSuiteName(crypto.cipher_suite)) ||
307 rtc::CS_AES_CM_128_HMAC_SHA1_80 == crypto.cipher_suite ||
308 (rtc::CS_AES_CM_128_HMAC_SHA1_32 == crypto.cipher_suite && audio &&
309 !bundle && crypto_options.srtp.enable_aes128_sha1_32_crypto_cipher)) {
310 return CreateCryptoParams(crypto.tag, crypto.cipher_suite, crypto_out);
311 }
312 }
313 return false;
314}

316// Finds all StreamParams of all media types and attach them to stream_params.
317static StreamParamsVec GetCurrentStreamParams(
318 const std::vector<const ContentInfo*>& active_local_contents) {
319 StreamParamsVec stream_params;
320 for (const ContentInfo* content : active_local_contents) {
321 for (const StreamParams& params : content->media_description()->streams()) {
322 stream_params.push_back(params);
323 }
324 }
325 return stream_params;

328static StreamParams CreateStreamParamsForNewSenderWithSsrcs(
329 const SenderOptions& sender,
330 const std::string& rtcp_cname,
331 bool include_rtx_streams,
332 bool include_flexfec_stream,
333 UniqueRandomIdGenerator* ssrc_generator) {
334 StreamParams result;
335 result.id = sender.track_id;
336
337 // TODO(brandtr): Update when we support multistream protection.
338 if (include_flexfec_stream && sender.num_sim_layers > 1) {
339 include_flexfec_stream = false;
340 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING)
341 << "Our FlexFEC implementation only supports protecting "
342 "a single media streams. This session has multiple "
343 "media streams however, so no FlexFEC SSRC will be generated.";
344 }
345 if (include_flexfec_stream &&
346 !webrtc::field_trial::IsEnabled("WebRTC-FlexFEC-03")) {
347 include_flexfec_stream = false;
348 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING)
349 << "WebRTC-FlexFEC trial is not enabled, not sending FlexFEC";
350 }
351
352 result.GenerateSsrcs(sender.num_sim_layers, include_rtx_streams,
353 include_flexfec_stream, ssrc_generator);
354
355 result.cname = rtcp_cname;
356 result.set_stream_ids(sender.stream_ids);
357
358 return result;
359}

361static bool ValidateSimulcastLayers(
362 const std::vector<RidDescription>& rids,
363 const SimulcastLayerList& simulcast_layers) {
364 return absl::c_all_of(
365 simulcast_layers.GetAllLayers(), [&rids](const SimulcastLayer& layer) {
366 return absl::c_any_of(rids, [&layer](const RidDescription& rid) {
367 return rid.rid == layer.rid;
368 });
369 });
370}
371
372static StreamParams CreateStreamParamsForNewSenderWithRids(
373 const SenderOptions& sender,
374 const std::string& rtcp_cname) {
375 RTC_DCHECK(!sender.rids.empty());
376 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(sender.num_sim_layers, 0)
377 << "RIDs are the compliant way to indicate simulcast.";
378 RTC_DCHECK(ValidateSimulcastLayers(sender.rids, sender.simulcast_layers));
379 StreamParams result;
380 result.id = sender.track_id;
381 result.cname = rtcp_cname;
382 result.set_stream_ids(sender.stream_ids);
383
384 // More than one rid should be signaled.
385 if (sender.rids.size() > 1) {
386 result.set_rids(sender.rids);
387 }
388
389 return result;
390}

392// Adds SimulcastDescription if indicated by the media description options.
393// MediaContentDescription should already be set up with the send rids.
394static void AddSimulcastToMediaDescription(
395 const MediaDescriptionOptions& media_description_options,
396 MediaContentDescription* description) {
397 RTC_DCHECK(description);
398
399 // Check if we are using RIDs in this scenario.
400 if (absl::c_all_of(description->streams(), [](const StreamParams& params) {
401 return !params.has_rids();
402 })) {
403 return;
404 }
405
406 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(1, description->streams().size())
407 << "RIDs are only supported in Unified Plan semantics.";
408 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(1, media_description_options.sender_options.size());
409 RTC_DCHECK(description->type() == MediaType::MEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO ||
410 description->type() == MediaType::MEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO);
411
412 // One RID or less indicates that simulcast is not needed.
413 if (description->streams()[0].rids().size() <= 1) {
414 return;
415 }
416
417 // Only negotiate the send layers.
418 SimulcastDescription simulcast;
419 simulcast.send_layers() =
420 media_description_options.sender_options[0].simulcast_layers;
421 description->set_simulcast_description(simulcast);
422}

424// Adds a StreamParams for each SenderOptions in |sender_options| to
425// content_description.
426// |current_params| - All currently known StreamParams of any media type.
427template <class C>
428static bool AddStreamParams(
429 const std::vector<SenderOptions>& sender_options,
430 const std::string& rtcp_cname,
431 UniqueRandomIdGenerator* ssrc_generator,
432 StreamParamsVec* current_streams,
433 MediaContentDescriptionImpl<C>* content_description) {
434 // SCTP streams are not negotiated using SDP/ContentDescriptions.
435 if (IsSctpProtocol(content_description->protocol())) {
436 return true;
437 }
438
439 const bool include_rtx_streams =
440 ContainsRtxCodec(content_description->codecs());
441
442 const bool include_flexfec_stream =
443 ContainsFlexfecCodec(content_description->codecs());
444
445 for (const SenderOptions& sender : sender_options) {
446 // groupid is empty for StreamParams generated using
447 // MediaSessionDescriptionFactory.
448 StreamParams* param =
449 GetStreamByIds(*current_streams, "" /*group_id*/, sender.track_id);
450 if (!param) {
451 // This is a new sender.
452 StreamParams stream_param =
453 sender.rids.empty()
454 ?
455 // Signal SSRCs and legacy simulcast (if requested).
456 CreateStreamParamsForNewSenderWithSsrcs(
457 sender, rtcp_cname, include_rtx_streams,
458 include_flexfec_stream, ssrc_generator)
459 :
460 // Signal RIDs and spec-compliant simulcast (if requested).
461 CreateStreamParamsForNewSenderWithRids(sender, rtcp_cname);
462
463 content_description->AddStream(stream_param);
464
465 // Store the new StreamParams in current_streams.
466 // This is necessary so that we can use the CNAME for other media types.
467 current_streams->push_back(stream_param);
468 } else {
469 // Use existing generated SSRCs/groups, but update the sync_label if
470 // necessary. This may be needed if a MediaStreamTrack was moved from one
471 // MediaStream to another.
472 param->set_stream_ids(sender.stream_ids);
473 content_description->AddStream(*param);
474 }
475 }
476 return true;
477}

479// Updates the transport infos of the |sdesc| according to the given
480// |bundle_group|. The transport infos of the content names within the
481// |bundle_group| should be updated to use the ufrag, pwd and DTLS role of the
482// first content within the |bundle_group|.
483static bool UpdateTransportInfoForBundle(const ContentGroup& bundle_group,
484 SessionDescription* sdesc) {
485 // The bundle should not be empty.
486 if (!sdesc || !bundle_group.FirstContentName()) {
487 return false;
488 }
489
490 // We should definitely have a transport for the first content.
491 const std::string& selected_content_name = *bundle_group.FirstContentName();
492 const TransportInfo* selected_transport_info =
493 sdesc->GetTransportInfoByName(selected_content_name);
494 if (!selected_transport_info) {
495 return false;
496 }
497
498 // Set the other contents to use the same ICE credentials.
499 const std::string& selected_ufrag =
500 selected_transport_info->description.ice_ufrag;
501 const std::string& selected_pwd =
502 selected_transport_info->description.ice_pwd;
503 ConnectionRole selected_connection_role =
504 selected_transport_info->description.connection_role;
505 for (TransportInfo& transport_info : sdesc->transport_infos()) {
506 if (bundle_group.HasContentName(transport_info.content_name) &&
507 transport_info.content_name != selected_content_name) {
508 transport_info.description.ice_ufrag = selected_ufrag;
509 transport_info.description.ice_pwd = selected_pwd;
510 transport_info.description.connection_role = selected_connection_role;
511 }
512 }
513 return true;
514}

516// Gets the CryptoParamsVec of the given |content_name| from |sdesc|, and
517// sets it to |cryptos|.
518static bool GetCryptosByName(const SessionDescription* sdesc,
519 const std::string& content_name,
520 CryptoParamsVec* cryptos) {
521 if (!sdesc || !cryptos) {
522 return false;
523 }
524 const ContentInfo* content = sdesc->GetContentByName(content_name);
525 if (!content || !content->media_description()) {
526 return false;
527 }
528 *cryptos = content->media_description()->cryptos();
529 return true;
530}
531
532// Prunes the |target_cryptos| by removing the crypto params (cipher_suite)
533// which are not available in |filter|.
534static void PruneCryptos(const CryptoParamsVec& filter,
535 CryptoParamsVec* target_cryptos) {
536 if (!target_cryptos) {
537 return;
538 }
539
540 target_cryptos->erase(
541 std::remove_if(target_cryptos->begin(), target_cryptos->end(),
542 // Returns true if the |crypto|'s cipher_suite is not
543 // found in |filter|.
544 [&filter](const CryptoParams& crypto) {
545 for (const CryptoParams& entry : filter) {
546 if (entry.cipher_suite == crypto.cipher_suite)
547 return false;
548 }
549 return true;
550 }),
551 target_cryptos->end());
552}

554static bool IsRtpContent(SessionDescription* sdesc,
555 const std::string& content_name) {
556 bool is_rtp = false;
557 ContentInfo* content = sdesc->GetContentByName(content_name);
558 if (content && content->media_description()) {
559 is_rtp = IsRtpProtocol(content->media_description()->protocol());
560 }
561 return is_rtp;
562}
563
564// Updates the crypto parameters of the |sdesc| according to the given
565// |bundle_group|. The crypto parameters of all the contents within the
566// |bundle_group| should be updated to use the common subset of the
567// available cryptos.
568static bool UpdateCryptoParamsForBundle(const ContentGroup& bundle_group,
569 SessionDescription* sdesc) {
570 // The bundle should not be empty.
571 if (!sdesc || !bundle_group.FirstContentName()) {
572 return false;
573 }
574
575 bool common_cryptos_needed = false;
576 // Get the common cryptos.
577 const ContentNames& content_names = bundle_group.content_names();
578 CryptoParamsVec common_cryptos;
579 bool first = true;
580 for (const std::string& content_name : content_names) {
581 if (!IsRtpContent(sdesc, content_name)) {
582 continue;
583 }
584 // The common cryptos are needed if any of the content does not have DTLS
585 // enabled.
586 if (!sdesc->GetTransportInfoByName(content_name)->description.secure()) {
587 common_cryptos_needed = true;
588 }
589 if (first) {
590 first = false;
591 // Initial the common_cryptos with the first content in the bundle group.
592 if (!GetCryptosByName(sdesc, content_name, &common_cryptos)) {
593 return false;
594 }
595 if (common_cryptos.empty()) {
596 // If there's no crypto params, we should just return.
597 return true;
598 }
599 } else {
600 CryptoParamsVec cryptos;
601 if (!GetCryptosByName(sdesc, content_name, &cryptos)) {
602 return false;
603 }
604 PruneCryptos(cryptos, &common_cryptos);
605 }
606 }
607
608 if (common_cryptos.empty() && common_cryptos_needed) {
609 return false;
610 }
611
612 // Update to use the common cryptos.
613 for (const std::string& content_name : content_names) {
614 if (!IsRtpContent(sdesc, content_name)) {
615 continue;
616 }
617 ContentInfo* content = sdesc->GetContentByName(content_name);
618 if (IsMediaContent(content)) {
619 MediaContentDescription* media_desc = content->media_description();
620 if (!media_desc) {
621 return false;
622 }
623 media_desc->set_cryptos(common_cryptos);
624 }
625 }
626 return true;
627}

629static std::vector<const ContentInfo*> GetActiveContents(
630 const SessionDescription& description,
631 const MediaSessionOptions& session_options) {
632 std::vector<const ContentInfo*> active_contents;
633 for (size_t i = 0; i < description.contents().size(); ++i) {
634 RTC_DCHECK_LT(i, session_options.media_description_options.size());
635 const ContentInfo& content = description.contents()[i];
636 const MediaDescriptionOptions& media_options =
637 session_options.media_description_options[i];
638 if (!content.rejected && !media_options.stopped &&
639 content.name == media_options.mid) {
640 active_contents.push_back(&content);
641 }
642 }
643 return active_contents;
644}

646template <class C>
647static bool ContainsRtxCodec(const std::vector<C>& codecs) {
648 for (const auto& codec : codecs) {
649 if (IsRtxCodec(codec)) {
650 return true;
651 }
652 }
653 return false;
654}
655
656template <class C>
657static bool IsRtxCodec(const C& codec) {
658 return absl::EqualsIgnoreCase(codec.name, kRtxCodecName);
659}
660
661template <class C>
662static bool ContainsFlexfecCodec(const std::vector<C>& codecs) {
663 for (const auto& codec : codecs) {
664 if (IsFlexfecCodec(codec)) {
665 return true;
666 }
667 }
668 return false;
669}
670
671template <class C>
672static bool IsFlexfecCodec(const C& codec) {
673 return absl::EqualsIgnoreCase(codec.name, kFlexfecCodecName);
674}
675
676// Create a media content to be offered for the given |sender_options|,
677// according to the given options.rtcp_mux, session_options.is_muc, codecs,
678// secure_transport, crypto, and current_streams. If we don't currently have
679// crypto (in current_cryptos) and it is enabled (in secure_policy), crypto is
680// created (according to crypto_suites). The created content is added to the
681// offer.
682static bool CreateContentOffer(
683 const MediaDescriptionOptions& media_description_options,
684 const MediaSessionOptions& session_options,
685 const SecurePolicy& secure_policy,
686 const CryptoParamsVec* current_cryptos,
687 const std::vector<std::string>& crypto_suites,
688 const RtpHeaderExtensions& rtp_extensions,
689 UniqueRandomIdGenerator* ssrc_generator,
690 StreamParamsVec* current_streams,
691 MediaContentDescription* offer) {
692 offer->set_rtcp_mux(session_options.rtcp_mux_enabled);
693 if (offer->type() == cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO) {
694 offer->set_rtcp_reduced_size(true);
695 }
696
697 // Build the vector of header extensions with directions for this
698 // media_description's options.
699 RtpHeaderExtensions extensions;
700 for (auto extension_with_id : rtp_extensions) {
701 for (const auto& extension : media_description_options.header_extensions) {
702 if (extension_with_id.uri == extension.uri) {
703 // TODO(crbug.com/1051821): Configure the extension direction from
704 // the information in the media_description_options extension
705 // capability.
706 extensions.push_back(extension_with_id);
707 }
708 }
709 }
710 offer->set_rtp_header_extensions(extensions);
711
712 AddSimulcastToMediaDescription(media_description_options, offer);
713
714 if (secure_policy != SEC_DISABLED) {
715 if (current_cryptos) {
716 AddMediaCryptos(*current_cryptos, offer);
717 }
718 if (offer->cryptos().empty()) {
719 if (!CreateMediaCryptos(crypto_suites, offer)) {
720 return false;
721 }
722 }
723 }
724
725 if (secure_policy == SEC_REQUIRED && offer->cryptos().empty()) {
726 return false;
727 }
728 return true;
729}
730template <class C>
731static bool CreateMediaContentOffer(
732 const MediaDescriptionOptions& media_description_options,
733 const MediaSessionOptions& session_options,
734 const std::vector<C>& codecs,
735 const SecurePolicy& secure_policy,
736 const CryptoParamsVec* current_cryptos,
737 const std::vector<std::string>& crypto_suites,
738 const RtpHeaderExtensions& rtp_extensions,
739 UniqueRandomIdGenerator* ssrc_generator,
740 StreamParamsVec* current_streams,
741 MediaContentDescriptionImpl<C>* offer) {
742 offer->AddCodecs(codecs);
743 if (!AddStreamParams(media_description_options.sender_options,
744 session_options.rtcp_cname, ssrc_generator,
745 current_streams, offer)) {
746 return false;
747 }
748
749 return CreateContentOffer(media_description_options, session_options,
750 secure_policy, current_cryptos, crypto_suites,
751 rtp_extensions, ssrc_generator, current_streams,
752 offer);
753}

755template <class C>
756static bool ReferencedCodecsMatch(const std::vector<C>& codecs1,
757 const int codec1_id,
758 const std::vector<C>& codecs2,
759 const int codec2_id) {
760 const C* codec1 = FindCodecById(codecs1, codec1_id);
761 const C* codec2 = FindCodecById(codecs2, codec2_id);
762 return codec1 != nullptr && codec2 != nullptr && codec1->Matches(*codec2);
763}

767 const C& remote_codec,
768 C* negotiated_codec) {}

777
778template <class C>
779static void NegotiateCodecs(const std::vector<C>& local_codecs,
780 const std::vector<C>& offered_codecs,
781 std::vector<C>* negotiated_codecs,
782 bool keep_offer_order) {
783 for (const C& ours : local_codecs) {
784 C theirs;
785 // Note that we intentionally only find one matching codec for each of our
786 // local codecs, in case the remote offer contains duplicate codecs.
787 if (FindMatchingCodec(local_codecs, offered_codecs, ours, &theirs)) {
788 C negotiated = ours;
789 NegotiatePacketization(ours, theirs, &negotiated);
790 negotiated.IntersectFeedbackParams(theirs);
791 if (IsRtxCodec(negotiated)) {
792 const auto apt_it =
793 theirs.params.find(kCodecParamAssociatedPayloadType);
794 // FindMatchingCodec shouldn't return something with no apt value.
795 RTC_DCHECK(apt_it != theirs.params.end());
796 negotiated.SetParam(kCodecParamAssociatedPayloadType, apt_it->second);
797
798 // We support parsing the declarative rtx-time parameter.
799 const auto rtx_time_it = theirs.params.find(kCodecParamRtxTime);
800 if (rtx_time_it != theirs.params.end()) {
801 negotiated.SetParam(kCodecParamRtxTime, rtx_time_it->second);
802 }
803 }
804 if (absl::EqualsIgnoreCase(ours.name, kH264CodecName)) {
805 webrtc::H264GenerateProfileLevelIdForAnswer(ours.params, theirs.params,
806 &negotiated.params);
807 }
808 negotiated.id = theirs.id;
809 negotiated.name = theirs.name;
810 negotiated_codecs->push_back(std::move(negotiated));
811 }
812 }
813 if (keep_offer_order) {
814 // RFC3264: Although the answerer MAY list the formats in their desired
815 // order of preference, it is RECOMMENDED that unless there is a
816 // specific reason, the answerer list formats in the same relative order
817 // they were present in the offer.
818 // This can be skipped when the transceiver has any codec preferences.
819 std::unordered_map<int, int> payload_type_preferences;
820 int preference = static_cast<int>(offered_codecs.size() + 1);
821 for (const C& codec : offered_codecs) {
822 payload_type_preferences[codec.id] = preference--;
823 }
824 absl::c_sort(*negotiated_codecs, [&payload_type_preferences](const C& a,
825 const C& b) {
826 return payload_type_preferences[a.id] > payload_type_preferences[b.id];
827 });
828 }
829}
830
831// Finds a codec in |codecs2| that matches |codec_to_match|, which is
832// a member of |codecs1|. If |codec_to_match| is an RTX codec, both
833// the codecs themselves and their associated codecs must match.
834template <class C>
835static bool FindMatchingCodec(const std::vector<C>& codecs1,
836 const std::vector<C>& codecs2,
837 const C& codec_to_match,
838 C* found_codec) {
839 // |codec_to_match| should be a member of |codecs1|, in order to look up RTX
840 // codecs' associated codecs correctly. If not, that's a programming error.
841 RTC_DCHECK(absl::c_any_of(codecs1, [&codec_to_match](const C& codec) {
842 return &codec == &codec_to_match;
843 }));
844 for (const C& potential_match : codecs2) {
845 if (potential_match.Matches(codec_to_match)) {
846 if (IsRtxCodec(codec_to_match)) {
847 int apt_value_1 = 0;
848 int apt_value_2 = 0;
849 if (!codec_to_match.GetParam(kCodecParamAssociatedPayloadType,
850 &apt_value_1) ||
851 !potential_match.GetParam(kCodecParamAssociatedPayloadType,
852 &apt_value_2)) {
853 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "RTX missing associated payload type.";
854 continue;
855 }
856 if (!ReferencedCodecsMatch(codecs1, apt_value_1, codecs2,
857 apt_value_2)) {
858 continue;
859 }
860 }
861 if (found_codec) {
862 *found_codec = potential_match;
863 }
864 return true;
865 }
866 }
867 return false;
868}
869
870// Find the codec in |codec_list| that |rtx_codec| is associated with.
871template <class C>
872static const C* GetAssociatedCodec(const std::vector<C>& codec_list,
873 const C& rtx_codec) {
874 std::string associated_pt_str;
875 if (!rtx_codec.GetParam(kCodecParamAssociatedPayloadType,
876 &associated_pt_str)) {
877 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "RTX codec " << rtx_codec.name
878 << " is missing an associated payload type.";
879 return nullptr;
880 }
881
882 int associated_pt;
883 if (!rtc::FromString(associated_pt_str, &associated_pt)) {
884 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Couldn't convert payload type " << associated_pt_str
885 << " of RTX codec " << rtx_codec.name
886 << " to an integer.";
887 return nullptr;
888 }
889
890 // Find the associated reference codec for the reference RTX codec.
891 const C* associated_codec = FindCodecById(codec_list, associated_pt);
892 if (!associated_codec) {
893 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Couldn't find associated codec with payload type "
894 << associated_pt << " for RTX codec " << rtx_codec.name
895 << ".";
896 }
897 return associated_codec;
898}
899
900// Adds all codecs from |reference_codecs| to |offered_codecs| that don't
901// already exist in |offered_codecs| and ensure the payload types don't
902// collide.
903template <class C>
904static void MergeCodecs(const std::vector<C>& reference_codecs,
905 std::vector<C>* offered_codecs,
906 UsedPayloadTypes* used_pltypes) {
907 // Add all new codecs that are not RTX codecs.
908 for (const C& reference_codec : reference_codecs) {
909 if (!IsRtxCodec(reference_codec) &&
910 !FindMatchingCodec<C>(reference_codecs, *offered_codecs,
911 reference_codec, nullptr)) {
912 C codec = reference_codec;
913 used_pltypes->FindAndSetIdUsed(&codec);
914 offered_codecs->push_back(codec);
915 }
916 }
917
918 // Add all new RTX codecs.
919 for (const C& reference_codec : reference_codecs) {
920 if (IsRtxCodec(reference_codec) &&
921 !FindMatchingCodec<C>(reference_codecs, *offered_codecs,
922 reference_codec, nullptr)) {
923 C rtx_codec = reference_codec;
924 const C* associated_codec =
925 GetAssociatedCodec(reference_codecs, rtx_codec);
926 if (!associated_codec) {
927 continue;
928 }
929 // Find a codec in the offered list that matches the reference codec.
930 // Its payload type may be different than the reference codec.
931 C matching_codec;
932 if (!FindMatchingCodec<C>(reference_codecs, *offered_codecs,
933 *associated_codec, &matching_codec)) {
934 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING)
935 << "Couldn't find matching " << associated_codec->name << " codec.";
936 continue;
937 }
938
939 rtx_codec.params[kCodecParamAssociatedPayloadType] =
940 rtc::ToString(matching_codec.id);
941 used_pltypes->FindAndSetIdUsed(&rtx_codec);
942 offered_codecs->push_back(rtx_codec);
943 }
944 }
945}
946
947template <typename Codecs>
948static Codecs MatchCodecPreference(
949 const std::vector<webrtc::RtpCodecCapability>& codec_preferences,
950 const Codecs& codecs) {
951 Codecs filtered_codecs;
952 std::set<std::string> kept_codecs_ids;
953 bool want_rtx = false;
954
955 for (const auto& codec_preference : codec_preferences) {
956 auto found_codec = absl::c_find_if(
957 codecs, [&codec_preference](const typename Codecs::value_type& codec) {
958 webrtc::RtpCodecParameters codec_parameters =
959 codec.ToCodecParameters();
960 return codec_parameters.name == codec_preference.name &&
961 codec_parameters.kind == codec_preference.kind &&
962 codec_parameters.num_channels ==
963 codec_preference.num_channels &&
964 codec_parameters.clock_rate == codec_preference.clock_rate &&
965 codec_parameters.parameters == codec_preference.parameters;
966 });
967
968 if (found_codec != codecs.end()) {
969 filtered_codecs.push_back(*found_codec);
970 kept_codecs_ids.insert(std::to_string(found_codec->id));
971 } else if (IsRtxCodec(codec_preference)) {
972 want_rtx = true;
973 }
974 }
975
976 if (want_rtx) {
977 for (const auto& codec : codecs) {
978 if (IsRtxCodec(codec)) {
979 const auto apt =
980 codec.params.find(cricket::kCodecParamAssociatedPayloadType);
981 if (apt != codec.params.end() &&
982 kept_codecs_ids.count(apt->second) > 0) {
983 filtered_codecs.push_back(codec);
984 }
985 }
986 }
987 }
988
989 return filtered_codecs;
990}
991
992static bool FindByUriAndEncryption(const RtpHeaderExtensions& extensions,
993 const webrtc::RtpExtension& ext_to_match,
994 webrtc::RtpExtension* found_extension) {
995 auto it = absl::c_find_if(
996 extensions, [&ext_to_match](const webrtc::RtpExtension& extension) {
997 // We assume that all URIs are given in a canonical
998 // format.
999 return extension.uri == ext_to_match.uri &&
1000 extension.encrypt == ext_to_match.encrypt;
1001 });
1002 if (it == extensions.end()) {
1003 return false;
1004 }
1005 if (found_extension) {
1006 *found_extension = *it;
1007 }
1008 return true;
1009}
1010
1011static bool FindByUri(const RtpHeaderExtensions& extensions,
1012 const webrtc::RtpExtension& ext_to_match,
1013 webrtc::RtpExtension* found_extension) {
1014 // We assume that all URIs are given in a canonical format.
1015 const webrtc::RtpExtension* found =
1016 webrtc::RtpExtension::FindHeaderExtensionByUri(extensions,
1017 ext_to_match.uri);
1018 if (!found) {
1019 return false;
1020 }
1021 if (found_extension) {
1022 *found_extension = *found;
1023 }
1024 return true;
1025}
1026
1027static bool FindByUriWithEncryptionPreference(
1028 const RtpHeaderExtensions& extensions,
1029 absl::string_view uri_to_match,
1030 bool encryption_preference,
1031 webrtc::RtpExtension* found_extension) {
1032 const webrtc::RtpExtension* unencrypted_extension = nullptr;
1033 for (const webrtc::RtpExtension& extension : extensions) {
1034 // We assume that all URIs are given in a canonical format.
1035 if (extension.uri == uri_to_match) {
1036 if (!encryption_preference || extension.encrypt) {
1037 if (found_extension) {
1038 *found_extension = extension;
1039 }
1040 return true;
1041 }
1042 unencrypted_extension = &extension;
1043 }
1044 }
1045 if (unencrypted_extension) {
1046 if (found_extension) {
1047 *found_extension = *unencrypted_extension;
1048 }
1049 return true;
1050 }
1051 return false;
1052}
1053
1054// Adds all extensions from |reference_extensions| to |offered_extensions| that
1055// don't already exist in |offered_extensions| and ensure the IDs don't
1056// collide. If an extension is added, it's also added to |regular_extensions| or
1057// |encrypted_extensions|, and if the extension is in |regular_extensions| or
1058// |encrypted_extensions|, its ID is marked as used in |used_ids|.
1059// |offered_extensions| is for either audio or video while |regular_extensions|
1060// and |encrypted_extensions| are used for both audio and video. There could be
1061// overlap between audio extensions and video extensions.
1062static void MergeRtpHdrExts(const RtpHeaderExtensions& reference_extensions,
1063 RtpHeaderExtensions* offered_extensions,
1064 RtpHeaderExtensions* regular_extensions,
1065 RtpHeaderExtensions* encrypted_extensions,
1066 UsedRtpHeaderExtensionIds* used_ids) {
1067 for (auto reference_extension : reference_extensions) {
1068 if (!FindByUriAndEncryption(*offered_extensions, reference_extension,
1069 nullptr)) {
1070 webrtc::RtpExtension existing;
1071 if (reference_extension.encrypt) {
1072 if (FindByUriAndEncryption(*encrypted_extensions, reference_extension,
1073 &existing)) {
1074 offered_extensions->push_back(existing);
1075 } else {
1076 used_ids->FindAndSetIdUsed(&reference_extension);
1077 encrypted_extensions->push_back(reference_extension);
1078 offered_extensions->push_back(reference_extension);
1079 }
1080 } else {
1081 if (FindByUriAndEncryption(*regular_extensions, reference_extension,
1082 &existing)) {
1083 offered_extensions->push_back(existing);
1084 } else {
1085 used_ids->FindAndSetIdUsed(&reference_extension);
1086 regular_extensions->push_back(reference_extension);
1087 offered_extensions->push_back(reference_extension);
1088 }
1089 }
1090 }
1091 }
1092}
1093
1094static void AddEncryptedVersionsOfHdrExts(RtpHeaderExtensions* extensions,
1095 RtpHeaderExtensions* all_extensions,
1096 UsedRtpHeaderExtensionIds* used_ids) {
1097 RtpHeaderExtensions encrypted_extensions;
1098 for (const webrtc::RtpExtension& extension : *extensions) {
1099 webrtc::RtpExtension existing;
1100 // Don't add encrypted extensions again that were already included in a
1101 // previous offer or regular extensions that are also included as encrypted
1102 // extensions.
1103 if (extension.encrypt ||
1104 !webrtc::RtpExtension::IsEncryptionSupported(extension.uri) ||
1105 (FindByUriWithEncryptionPreference(*extensions, extension.uri, true,
1106 &existing) &&
1107 existing.encrypt)) {
1108 continue;
1109 }
1110
1111 if (FindByUri(*all_extensions, extension, &existing)) {
1112 encrypted_extensions.push_back(existing);
1113 } else {
1114 webrtc::RtpExtension encrypted(extension);
1115 encrypted.encrypt = true;
1116 used_ids->FindAndSetIdUsed(&encrypted);
1117 all_extensions->push_back(encrypted);
1118 encrypted_extensions.push_back(encrypted);
1119 }
1120 }
1121 extensions->insert(extensions->end(), encrypted_extensions.begin(),
1122 encrypted_extensions.end());
1123}
1124
1125static void NegotiateRtpHeaderExtensions(
1126 const RtpHeaderExtensions& local_extensions,
1127 const RtpHeaderExtensions& offered_extensions,
1128 bool enable_encrypted_rtp_header_extensions,
1129 RtpHeaderExtensions* negotiated_extensions) {
1130 // TransportSequenceNumberV2 is not offered by default. The special logic for
1131 // the TransportSequenceNumber extensions works as follows:
1132 // Offer Answer
1133 // V1 V1 if in local_extensions.
1134 // V1 and V2 V2 regardless of local_extensions.
1135 // V2 V2 regardless of local_extensions.
1136 const webrtc::RtpExtension* transport_sequence_number_v2_offer =
1137 webrtc::RtpExtension::FindHeaderExtensionByUri(
1138 offered_extensions,
1139 webrtc::RtpExtension::kTransportSequenceNumberV2Uri);
1140
1141 bool frame_descriptor_in_local = false;
1142 bool dependency_descriptor_in_local = false;
1143 bool abs_capture_time_in_local = false;
1144
1145 for (const webrtc::RtpExtension& ours : local_extensions) {
1146 if (ours.uri == webrtc::RtpExtension::kGenericFrameDescriptorUri00)
1147 frame_descriptor_in_local = true;
1148 else if (ours.uri == webrtc::RtpExtension::kDependencyDescriptorUri)
1149 dependency_descriptor_in_local = true;
1150 else if (ours.uri == webrtc::RtpExtension::kAbsoluteCaptureTimeUri)
1151 abs_capture_time_in_local = true;
1152 webrtc::RtpExtension theirs;
1153 if (FindByUriWithEncryptionPreference(
1154 offered_extensions, ours.uri,
1155 enable_encrypted_rtp_header_extensions, &theirs)) {
1156 if (transport_sequence_number_v2_offer &&
1157 ours.uri == webrtc::RtpExtension::kTransportSequenceNumberUri) {
1158 // Don't respond to
1159 // http://www.ietf.org/id/draft-holmer-rmcat-transport-wide-cc-extensions-01
1160 // if we get an offer including
1161 // http://www.webrtc.org/experiments/rtp-hdrext/transport-wide-cc-02
1162 continue;
1163 } else {
1164 // We respond with their RTP header extension id.
1165 negotiated_extensions->push_back(theirs);
1166 }
1167 }
1168 }
1169
1170 if (transport_sequence_number_v2_offer) {
1171 // Respond that we support kTransportSequenceNumberV2Uri.
1172 negotiated_extensions->push_back(*transport_sequence_number_v2_offer);
1173 }
1174
1175 // Frame descriptors support. If the extension is not present locally, but is
1176 // in the offer, we add it to the list.
1177 webrtc::RtpExtension theirs;
1178 if (!dependency_descriptor_in_local &&
1179 FindByUriWithEncryptionPreference(
1180 offered_extensions, webrtc::RtpExtension::kDependencyDescriptorUri,
1181 enable_encrypted_rtp_header_extensions, &theirs)) {
1182 negotiated_extensions->push_back(theirs);
1183 }
1184 if (!frame_descriptor_in_local &&
1185 FindByUriWithEncryptionPreference(
1186 offered_extensions,
1187 webrtc::RtpExtension::kGenericFrameDescriptorUri00,
1188 enable_encrypted_rtp_header_extensions, &theirs)) {
1189 negotiated_extensions->push_back(theirs);
1190 }
1191
1192 // Absolute capture time support. If the extension is not present locally, but
1193 // is in the offer, we add it to the list.
1194 if (!abs_capture_time_in_local &&
1195 FindByUriWithEncryptionPreference(
1196 offered_extensions, webrtc::RtpExtension::kAbsoluteCaptureTimeUri,
1197 enable_encrypted_rtp_header_extensions, &theirs)) {
1198 negotiated_extensions->push_back(theirs);
1199 }
1200}

1202static void StripCNCodecs(AudioCodecs* audio_codecs) {
1203 audio_codecs->erase(std::remove_if(audio_codecs->begin(), audio_codecs->end(),
1204 [](const AudioCodec& codec) {
1205 return absl::EqualsIgnoreCase(
1206 codec.name, kComfortNoiseCodecName);
1207 }),
1208 audio_codecs->end());
1209}
1210
1211template <class C>
1212static bool SetCodecsInAnswer(
1213 const MediaContentDescriptionImpl<C>* offer,
1214 const std::vector<C>& local_codecs,
1215 const MediaDescriptionOptions& media_description_options,
1216 const MediaSessionOptions& session_options,
1217 UniqueRandomIdGenerator* ssrc_generator,
1218 StreamParamsVec* current_streams,
1219 MediaContentDescriptionImpl<C>* answer) {
1220 std::vector<C> negotiated_codecs;
1221 NegotiateCodecs(local_codecs, offer->codecs(), &negotiated_codecs,
1222 media_description_options.codec_preferences.empty());
1223 answer->AddCodecs(negotiated_codecs);
1224 answer->set_protocol(offer->protocol());
1225 if (!AddStreamParams(media_description_options.sender_options,
1226 session_options.rtcp_cname, ssrc_generator,
1227 current_streams, answer)) {
1228 return false; // Something went seriously wrong.
1229 }
1230 return true;
1231}
1232
1233// Create a media content to be answered for the given |sender_options|
1234// according to the given session_options.rtcp_mux, session_options.streams,
1235// codecs, crypto, and current_streams. If we don't currently have crypto (in
1236// current_cryptos) and it is enabled (in secure_policy), crypto is created
1237// (according to crypto_suites). The codecs, rtcp_mux, and crypto are all
1238// negotiated with the offer. If the negotiation fails, this method returns
1239// false. The created content is added to the offer.
1240static bool CreateMediaContentAnswer(
1241 const MediaContentDescription* offer,
1242 const MediaDescriptionOptions& media_description_options,
1243 const MediaSessionOptions& session_options,
1244 const SecurePolicy& sdes_policy,
1245 const CryptoParamsVec* current_cryptos,
1246 const RtpHeaderExtensions& local_rtp_extensions,
1247 UniqueRandomIdGenerator* ssrc_generator,
1248 bool enable_encrypted_rtp_header_extensions,
1249 StreamParamsVec* current_streams,
1250 bool bundle_enabled,
1251 MediaContentDescription* answer) {
1252 answer->set_extmap_allow_mixed_enum(offer->extmap_allow_mixed_enum());
1253 RtpHeaderExtensions negotiated_rtp_extensions;
1254 NegotiateRtpHeaderExtensions(
1255 local_rtp_extensions, offer->rtp_header_extensions(),
1256 enable_encrypted_rtp_header_extensions, &negotiated_rtp_extensions);
1257 answer->set_rtp_header_extensions(negotiated_rtp_extensions);
1258
1259 answer->set_rtcp_mux(session_options.rtcp_mux_enabled && offer->rtcp_mux());
1260 if (answer->type() == cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO) {
1261 answer->set_rtcp_reduced_size(offer->rtcp_reduced_size());
1262 }
1263
1264 answer->set_remote_estimate(offer->remote_estimate());
1265
1266 if (sdes_policy != SEC_DISABLED) {
1267 CryptoParams crypto;
1268 if (SelectCrypto(offer, bundle_enabled, session_options.crypto_options,
1269 &crypto)) {
1270 if (current_cryptos) {
1271 FindMatchingCrypto(*current_cryptos, crypto, &crypto);
1272 }
1273 answer->AddCrypto(crypto);
1274 }
1275 }
1276
1277 if (answer->cryptos().empty() && sdes_policy == SEC_REQUIRED) {
1278 return false;
1279 }
1280
1281 AddSimulcastToMediaDescription(media_description_options, answer);
1282
1283 answer->set_direction(NegotiateRtpTransceiverDirection(
1284 offer->direction(), media_description_options.direction));
1285
1286 return true;
1287}
1288
1289static bool IsMediaProtocolSupported(MediaType type,
1290 const std::string& protocol,
1291 bool secure_transport) {
1292 // Since not all applications serialize and deserialize the media protocol,
1293 // we will have to accept |protocol| to be empty.
1294 if (protocol.empty()) {
1295 return true;
1296 }
1297
1298 if (type == MEDIA_TYPE_DATA) {
1299 // Check for SCTP, but also for RTP for RTP-based data channels.
1300 // TODO(pthatcher): Remove RTP once RTP-based data channels are gone.
1301 if (secure_transport) {
1302 // Most likely scenarios first.
1303 return IsDtlsSctp(protocol) || IsDtlsRtp(protocol) ||
1304 IsPlainRtp(protocol);
1305 } else {
1306 return IsPlainSctp(protocol) || IsPlainRtp(protocol);
1307 }
1308 }
1309
1310 // Allow for non-DTLS RTP protocol even when using DTLS because that's what
1311 // JSEP specifies.
1312 if (secure_transport) {
1313 // Most likely scenarios first.
1314 return IsDtlsRtp(protocol) || IsPlainRtp(protocol);
1315 } else {
1316 return IsPlainRtp(protocol);
1317 }
1318}
1319
1320static void SetMediaProtocol(bool secure_transport,
1321 MediaContentDescription* desc) {
1322 if (!desc->cryptos().empty())
1323 desc->set_protocol(kMediaProtocolSavpf);
1324 else if (secure_transport)
1325 desc->set_protocol(kMediaProtocolDtlsSavpf);
1326 else
1327 desc->set_protocol(kMediaProtocolAvpf);
1328}
1329
1330// Gets the TransportInfo of the given |content_name| from the
1331// |current_description|. If doesn't exist, returns a new one.
1332static const TransportDescription* GetTransportDescription(
1333 const std::string& content_name,
1334 const SessionDescription* current_description) {
1335 const TransportDescription* desc = NULL;
1336 if (current_description) {
1337 const TransportInfo* info =
1338 current_description->GetTransportInfoByName(content_name);
1339 if (info) {
1340 desc = &info->description;
1341 }
1342 }
1343 return desc;
1344}
1345
1346// Gets the current DTLS state from the transport description.
1347static bool IsDtlsActive(const ContentInfo* content,
1348 const SessionDescription* current_description) {
1349 if (!content) {
1350 return false;
1351 }
1352
1353 size_t msection_index = content - &current_description->contents()[0];
1354
1355 if (current_description->transport_infos().size() <= msection_index) {
1356 return false;
1357 }
1358
1359 return current_description->transport_infos()[msection_index]
1360 .description.secure();
1361}

1470static void RemoveUnifiedPlanExtensions(RtpHeaderExtensions* extensions) {
1471 RTC_DCHECK(extensions);
1472
1473 extensions->erase(
1474 std::remove_if(extensions->begin(), extensions->end(),
1475 [](auto extension) {
1476 return extension.uri == webrtc::RtpExtension::kMidUri ||
1477 extension.uri == webrtc::RtpExtension::kRidUri ||
1478 extension.uri ==
1479 webrtc::RtpExtension::kRepairedRidUri;
1480 }),
1481 extensions->end());
1482}

1492
1493std::unique_ptr<SessionDescription> MediaSessionDescriptionFactory::CreateOffer(
1494 const MediaSessionOptions& session_options,
1495 const SessionDescription* current_description) const {
1496 // Must have options for each existing section.
1497 if (current_description) {
1498 RTC_DCHECK_LE(current_description->contents().size(),
1499 session_options.media_description_options.size());
1500 }
1501
1502 IceCredentialsIterator ice_credentials(
1503 session_options.pooled_ice_credentials);
1504
1505 std::vector<const ContentInfo*> current_active_contents;
1506 if (current_description) {
1507 current_active_contents =
1508 GetActiveContents(*current_description, session_options);
1509 }
1510
1511 StreamParamsVec current_streams =
1512 GetCurrentStreamParams(current_active_contents);
1513
1514 AudioCodecs offer_audio_codecs;
1515 VideoCodecs offer_video_codecs;
1516 GetCodecsForOffer(current_active_contents, &offer_audio_codecs,
1517 &offer_video_codecs);
1518 AudioVideoRtpHeaderExtensions extensions_with_ids =
1519 GetOfferedRtpHeaderExtensionsWithIds(
1520 current_active_contents, session_options.offer_extmap_allow_mixed,
1521 session_options.media_description_options);
1522
1523 auto offer = std::make_unique<SessionDescription>();
1524
1525 // Iterate through the media description options, matching with existing media
1526 // descriptions in |current_description|.
1527 size_t msection_index = 0;
1528 for (const MediaDescriptionOptions& media_description_options :
1529 session_options.media_description_options) {
1530 const ContentInfo* current_content = nullptr;
1531 if (current_description &&
1532 msection_index < current_description->contents().size()) {
1533 current_content = &current_description->contents()[msection_index];
1534 // Media type must match unless this media section is being recycled.
1535 RTC_DCHECK(current_content->name != media_description_options.mid ||
1536 IsMediaContentOfType(current_content,
1537 media_description_options.type));
1538 }
1539 switch (media_description_options.type) {
1540 case MEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO:
1541 if (!AddAudioContentForOffer(media_description_options, session_options,
1542 current_content, current_description,
1543 extensions_with_ids.audio,
1544 offer_audio_codecs, &current_streams,
1545 offer.get(), &ice_credentials)) {
1546 return nullptr;
1547 }
1548 break;
1549 case MEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO:
1550 if (!AddVideoContentForOffer(media_description_options, session_options,
1551 current_content, current_description,
1552 extensions_with_ids.video,
1553 offer_video_codecs, &current_streams,
1554 offer.get(), &ice_credentials)) {
1555 return nullptr;
1556 }
1557 break;
1558 case MEDIA_TYPE_DATA:
1559 if (!AddDataContentForOffer(media_description_options, session_options,
1560 current_content, current_description,
1561 &current_streams, offer.get(),
1562 &ice_credentials)) {
1563 return nullptr;
1564 }
1565 break;
1566 case MEDIA_TYPE_UNSUPPORTED:
1567 if (!AddUnsupportedContentForOffer(
1568 media_description_options, session_options, current_content,
1569 current_description, offer.get(), &ice_credentials)) {
1570 return nullptr;
1571 }
1572 break;
1573 default:
1574 RTC_NOTREACHED();
1575 }
1576 ++msection_index;
1577 }
1578
1579 // Bundle the contents together, if we've been asked to do so, and update any
1580 // parameters that need to be tweaked for BUNDLE.
1581 if (session_options.bundle_enabled) {
1582 ContentGroup offer_bundle(GROUP_TYPE_BUNDLE);
1583 for (const ContentInfo& content : offer->contents()) {
1584 if (content.rejected) {
1585 continue;
1586 }
1587 // TODO(deadbeef): There are conditions that make bundling two media
1588 // descriptions together illegal. For example, they use the same payload
1589 // type to represent different codecs, or same IDs for different header
1590 // extensions. We need to detect this and not try to bundle those media
1591 // descriptions together.
1592 offer_bundle.AddContentName(content.name);
1593 }
1594 if (!offer_bundle.content_names().empty()) {
1595 offer->AddGroup(offer_bundle);
1596 if (!UpdateTransportInfoForBundle(offer_bundle, offer.get())) {
1597 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR)
1598 << "CreateOffer failed to UpdateTransportInfoForBundle.";
1599 return nullptr;
1600 }
1601 if (!UpdateCryptoParamsForBundle(offer_bundle, offer.get())) {
1602 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR)
1603 << "CreateOffer failed to UpdateCryptoParamsForBundle.";
1604 return nullptr;
1605 }
1606 }
1607 }
1608
1609 // The following determines how to signal MSIDs to ensure compatibility with
1610 // older endpoints (in particular, older Plan B endpoints).
1611 if (is_unified_plan_) {
1612 // Be conservative and signal using both a=msid and a=ssrc lines. Unified
1613 // Plan answerers will look at a=msid and Plan B answerers will look at the
1614 // a=ssrc MSID line.
1615 offer->set_msid_signaling(cricket::kMsidSignalingMediaSection |
1616 cricket::kMsidSignalingSsrcAttribute);
1617 } else {
1618 // Plan B always signals MSID using a=ssrc lines.
1619 offer->set_msid_signaling(cricket::kMsidSignalingSsrcAttribute);
1620 }
1621
1622 offer->set_extmap_allow_mixed(session_options.offer_extmap_allow_mixed);
1623
1624 return offer;
1625}
1626
1627std::unique_ptr<SessionDescription>
1628MediaSessionDescriptionFactory::CreateAnswer(
1629 const SessionDescription* offer,
1630 const MediaSessionOptions& session_options,
1631 const SessionDescription* current_description) const {
1632 if (!offer) {
1633 return nullptr;
1634 }
1635
1636 // Must have options for exactly as many sections as in the offer.
1637 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(offer->contents().size(),
1638 session_options.media_description_options.size());
1639
1640 IceCredentialsIterator ice_credentials(
1641 session_options.pooled_ice_credentials);
1642
1643 std::vector<const ContentInfo*> current_active_contents;
1644 if (current_description) {
1645 current_active_contents =
1646 GetActiveContents(*current_description, session_options);
1647 }
1648
1649 StreamParamsVec current_streams =
1650 GetCurrentStreamParams(current_active_contents);
1651
1652 // Get list of all possible codecs that respects existing payload type
1653 // mappings and uses a single payload type space.
1654 //
1655 // Note that these lists may be further filtered for each m= section; this
1656 // step is done just to establish the payload type mappings shared by all
1657 // sections.
1658 AudioCodecs answer_audio_codecs;
1659 VideoCodecs answer_video_codecs;
1660 GetCodecsForAnswer(current_active_contents, *offer, &answer_audio_codecs,
1661 &answer_video_codecs);
1662
1663 auto answer = std::make_unique<SessionDescription>();
1664
1665 // If the offer supports BUNDLE, and we want to use it too, create a BUNDLE
1666 // group in the answer with the appropriate content names.
1667 std::vector<const ContentGroup*> offer_bundles =
1668 offer->GetGroupsByName(GROUP_TYPE_BUNDLE);
1669 // There are as many answer BUNDLE groups as offer BUNDLE groups (even if
1670 // rejected, we respond with an empty group). |offer_bundles|,
1671 // |answer_bundles| and |bundle_transports| share the same size and indices.
1672 std::vector<ContentGroup> answer_bundles;
1673 std::vector<std::unique_ptr<TransportInfo>> bundle_transports;
1674 answer_bundles.reserve(offer_bundles.size());
1675 bundle_transports.reserve(offer_bundles.size());
1676 for (size_t i = 0; i < offer_bundles.size(); ++i) {
1677 answer_bundles.emplace_back(GROUP_TYPE_BUNDLE);
1678 bundle_transports.emplace_back(nullptr);
1679 }
1680
1681 answer->set_extmap_allow_mixed(offer->extmap_allow_mixed());
1682
1683 // Iterate through the media description options, matching with existing
1684 // media descriptions in |current_description|.
1685 size_t msection_index = 0;
1686 for (const MediaDescriptionOptions& media_description_options :
1687 session_options.media_description_options) {
1688 const ContentInfo* offer_content = &offer->contents()[msection_index];
1689 // Media types and MIDs must match between the remote offer and the
1690 // MediaDescriptionOptions.
1691 RTC_DCHECK(
1692 IsMediaContentOfType(offer_content, media_description_options.type));
1693 RTC_DCHECK(media_description_options.mid == offer_content->name);
1694 // Get the index of the BUNDLE group that this MID belongs to, if any.
1695 absl::optional<size_t> bundle_index;
1696 for (size_t i = 0; i < offer_bundles.size(); ++i) {
1697 if (offer_bundles[i]->HasContentName(media_description_options.mid)) {
1698 bundle_index = i;
1699 break;
1700 }
1701 }
1702 TransportInfo* bundle_transport =
1703 bundle_index.has_value() ? bundle_transports[bundle_index.value()].get()
1704 : nullptr;
1705
1706 const ContentInfo* current_content = nullptr;
1707 if (current_description &&
1708 msection_index < current_description->contents().size()) {
1709 current_content = &current_description->contents()[msection_index];
1710 }
1711 RtpHeaderExtensions header_extensions = RtpHeaderExtensionsFromCapabilities(
1712 UnstoppedRtpHeaderExtensionCapabilities(
1713 media_description_options.header_extensions));
1714 switch (media_description_options.type) {
1715 case MEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO:
1716 if (!AddAudioContentForAnswer(
1717 media_description_options, session_options, offer_content,
1718 offer, current_content, current_description, bundle_transport,
1719 answer_audio_codecs, header_extensions, &current_streams,
1720 answer.get(), &ice_credentials)) {
1721 return nullptr;
1722 }
1723 break;
1724 case MEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO:
1725 if (!AddVideoContentForAnswer(
1726 media_description_options, session_options, offer_content,
1727 offer, current_content, current_description, bundle_transport,
1728 answer_video_codecs, header_extensions, &current_streams,
1729 answer.get(), &ice_credentials)) {
1730 return nullptr;
1731 }
1732 break;
1733 case MEDIA_TYPE_DATA:
1734 if (!AddDataContentForAnswer(
1735 media_description_options, session_options, offer_content,
1736 offer, current_content, current_description, bundle_transport,
1737 &current_streams, answer.get(), &ice_credentials)) {
1738 return nullptr;
1739 }
1740 break;
1741 case MEDIA_TYPE_UNSUPPORTED:
1742 if (!AddUnsupportedContentForAnswer(
1743 media_description_options, session_options, offer_content,
1744 offer, current_content, current_description, bundle_transport,
1745 answer.get(), &ice_credentials)) {
1746 return nullptr;
1747 }
1748 break;
1749 default:
1750 RTC_NOTREACHED();
1751 }
1752 ++msection_index;
1753 // See if we can add the newly generated m= section to the BUNDLE group in
1754 // the answer.
1755 ContentInfo& added = answer->contents().back();
1756 if (!added.rejected && session_options.bundle_enabled &&
1757 bundle_index.has_value()) {
1758 // The |bundle_index| is for |media_description_options.mid|.
1759 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(media_description_options.mid, added.name);
1760 answer_bundles[bundle_index.value()].AddContentName(added.name);
1761 bundle_transports[bundle_index.value()].reset(
1762 new TransportInfo(*answer->GetTransportInfoByName(added.name)));
1763 }
1764 }
1765
1766 // If BUNDLE group(s) were offered, put the same number of BUNDLE groups in
1767 // the answer even if they're empty. RFC5888 says:
1768 //
1769 // A SIP entity that receives an offer that contains an "a=group" line
1770 // with semantics that are understood MUST return an answer that
1771 // contains an "a=group" line with the same semantics.
1772 if (!offer_bundles.empty()) {
1773 for (const ContentGroup& answer_bundle : answer_bundles) {
1774 answer->AddGroup(answer_bundle);
1775
1776 if (answer_bundle.FirstContentName()) {
1777 // Share the same ICE credentials and crypto params across all contents,
1778 // as BUNDLE requires.
1779 if (!UpdateTransportInfoForBundle(answer_bundle, answer.get())) {
1780 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR)
1781 << "CreateAnswer failed to UpdateTransportInfoForBundle.";
1782 return NULL;
1783 }
1784
1785 if (!UpdateCryptoParamsForBundle(answer_bundle, answer.get())) {
1786 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR)
1787 << "CreateAnswer failed to UpdateCryptoParamsForBundle.";
1788 return NULL;
1789 }
1790 }
1791 }
1792 }
1793
1794 // The following determines how to signal MSIDs to ensure compatibility with
1795 // older endpoints (in particular, older Plan B endpoints).
1796 if (is_unified_plan_) {
1797 // Unified Plan needs to look at what the offer included to find the most
1798 // compatible answer.
1799 if (offer->msid_signaling() == 0) {
1800 // We end up here in one of three cases:
1801 // 1. An empty offer. We'll reply with an empty answer so it doesn't
1802 // matter what we pick here.
1803 // 2. A data channel only offer. We won't add any MSIDs to the answer so
1804 // it also doesn't matter what we pick here.
1805 // 3. Media that's either sendonly or inactive from the remote endpoint.
1806 // We don't have any information to say whether the endpoint is Plan B
1807 // or Unified Plan, so be conservative and send both.
1808 answer->set_msid_signaling(cricket::kMsidSignalingMediaSection |
1809 cricket::kMsidSignalingSsrcAttribute);
1810 } else if (offer->msid_signaling() ==
1811 (cricket::kMsidSignalingMediaSection |
1812 cricket::kMsidSignalingSsrcAttribute)) {
1813 // If both a=msid and a=ssrc MSID signaling methods were used, we're
1814 // probably talking to a Unified Plan endpoint so respond with just
1815 // a=msid.
1816 answer->set_msid_signaling(cricket::kMsidSignalingMediaSection);
1817 } else {
1818 // Otherwise, it's clear which method the offerer is using so repeat that
1819 // back to them.
1820 answer->set_msid_signaling(offer->msid_signaling());
1821 }
1822 } else {
1823 // Plan B always signals MSID using a=ssrc lines.
1824 answer->set_msid_signaling(cricket::kMsidSignalingSsrcAttribute);
1825 }
1826
1827 return answer;
1828}

1834 case RtpTransceiverDirection::kSendRecv:
1835 case RtpTransceiverDirection::kStopped:
1836 case RtpTransceiverDirection::kInactive:

1899
1900void MergeCodecsFromDescription(
1901 const std::vector<const ContentInfo*>& current_active_contents,
1902 AudioCodecs* audio_codecs,
1903 VideoCodecs* video_codecs,
1904 UsedPayloadTypes* used_pltypes) {
1905 for (const ContentInfo* content : current_active_contents) {
1906 if (IsMediaContentOfType(content, MEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO)) {
1907 const AudioContentDescription* audio =
1908 content->media_description()->as_audio();
1909 MergeCodecs<AudioCodec>(audio->codecs(), audio_codecs, used_pltypes);
1910 } else if (IsMediaContentOfType(content, MEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO)) {
1911 const VideoContentDescription* video =
1912 content->media_description()->as_video();
1913 MergeCodecs<VideoCodec>(video->codecs(), video_codecs, used_pltypes);
1914 }
1915 }
1916}
1917
1918// Getting codecs for an offer involves these steps:
1919//
1920// 1. Construct payload type -> codec mappings for current description.
1921// 2. Add any reference codecs that weren't already present
1922// 3. For each individual media description (m= section), filter codecs based
1923// on the directional attribute (happens in another method).
1924void MediaSessionDescriptionFactory::GetCodecsForOffer(
1925 const std::vector<const ContentInfo*>& current_active_contents,
1926 AudioCodecs* audio_codecs,
1927 VideoCodecs* video_codecs) const {
1928 // First - get all codecs from the current description if the media type
1929 // is used. Add them to |used_pltypes| so the payload type is not reused if a
1930 // new media type is added.
1931 UsedPayloadTypes used_pltypes;
1932 MergeCodecsFromDescription(current_active_contents, audio_codecs,
1933 video_codecs, &used_pltypes);
1934
1935 // Add our codecs that are not in the current description.
1936 MergeCodecs<AudioCodec>(all_audio_codecs_, audio_codecs, &used_pltypes);
1937 MergeCodecs<VideoCodec>(all_video_codecs_, video_codecs, &used_pltypes);
1938}
1939
1940// Getting codecs for an answer involves these steps:
1941//
1942// 1. Construct payload type -> codec mappings for current description.
1943// 2. Add any codecs from the offer that weren't already present.
1944// 3. Add any remaining codecs that weren't already present.
1945// 4. For each individual media description (m= section), filter codecs based
1946// on the directional attribute (happens in another method).
1947void MediaSessionDescriptionFactory::GetCodecsForAnswer(
1948 const std::vector<const ContentInfo*>& current_active_contents,
1949 const SessionDescription& remote_offer,
1950 AudioCodecs* audio_codecs,
1951 VideoCodecs* video_codecs) const {
1952 // First - get all codecs from the current description if the media type
1953 // is used. Add them to |used_pltypes| so the payload type is not reused if a
1954 // new media type is added.
1955 UsedPayloadTypes used_pltypes;
1956 MergeCodecsFromDescription(current_active_contents, audio_codecs,
1957 video_codecs, &used_pltypes);
1958
1959 // Second - filter out codecs that we don't support at all and should ignore.
1960 AudioCodecs filtered_offered_audio_codecs;
1961 VideoCodecs filtered_offered_video_codecs;
1962 for (const ContentInfo& content : remote_offer.contents()) {
1963 if (IsMediaContentOfType(&content, MEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO)) {
1964 const AudioContentDescription* audio =
1965 content.media_description()->as_audio();
1966 for (const AudioCodec& offered_audio_codec : audio->codecs()) {
1967 if (!FindMatchingCodec<AudioCodec>(audio->codecs(),
1968 filtered_offered_audio_codecs,
1969 offered_audio_codec, nullptr) &&
1970 FindMatchingCodec<AudioCodec>(audio->codecs(), all_audio_codecs_,
1971 offered_audio_codec, nullptr)) {
1972 filtered_offered_audio_codecs.push_back(offered_audio_codec);
1973 }
1974 }
1975 } else if (IsMediaContentOfType(&content, MEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO)) {
1976 const VideoContentDescription* video =
1977 content.media_description()->as_video();
1978 for (const VideoCodec& offered_video_codec : video->codecs()) {
1979 if (!FindMatchingCodec<VideoCodec>(video->codecs(),
1980 filtered_offered_video_codecs,
1981 offered_video_codec, nullptr) &&
1982 FindMatchingCodec<VideoCodec>(video->codecs(), all_video_codecs_,
1983 offered_video_codec, nullptr)) {
1984 filtered_offered_video_codecs.push_back(offered_video_codec);
1985 }
1986 }
1987 }
1988 }
1989
1990 // Add codecs that are not in the current description but were in
1991 // |remote_offer|.
1992 MergeCodecs<AudioCodec>(filtered_offered_audio_codecs, audio_codecs,
1993 &used_pltypes);
1994 MergeCodecs<VideoCodec>(filtered_offered_video_codecs, video_codecs,
1995 &used_pltypes);
1996}
1997
1998MediaSessionDescriptionFactory::AudioVideoRtpHeaderExtensions
1999MediaSessionDescriptionFactory::GetOfferedRtpHeaderExtensionsWithIds(
2000 const std::vector<const ContentInfo*>& current_active_contents,
2001 bool extmap_allow_mixed,
2002 const std::vector<MediaDescriptionOptions>& media_description_options)
2003 const {
2004 // All header extensions allocated from the same range to avoid potential
2005 // issues when using BUNDLE.
2006
2007 // Strictly speaking the SDP attribute extmap_allow_mixed signals that the
2008 // receiver supports an RTP stream where one- and two-byte RTP header
2009 // extensions are mixed. For backwards compatibility reasons it's used in
2010 // WebRTC to signal that two-byte RTP header extensions are supported.
2011 UsedRtpHeaderExtensionIds used_ids(
2012 extmap_allow_mixed ? UsedRtpHeaderExtensionIds::IdDomain::kTwoByteAllowed
2013 : UsedRtpHeaderExtensionIds::IdDomain::kOneByteOnly);
2014 RtpHeaderExtensions all_regular_extensions;
2015 RtpHeaderExtensions all_encrypted_extensions;
2016
2017 AudioVideoRtpHeaderExtensions offered_extensions;
2018 // First - get all extensions from the current description if the media type
2019 // is used.
2020 // Add them to |used_ids| so the local ids are not reused if a new media
2021 // type is added.
2022 for (const ContentInfo* content : current_active_contents) {
2023 if (IsMediaContentOfType(content, MEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO)) {
2024 const AudioContentDescription* audio =
2025 content->media_description()->as_audio();
2026 MergeRtpHdrExts(audio->rtp_header_extensions(), &offered_extensions.audio,
2027 &all_regular_extensions, &all_encrypted_extensions,
2028 &used_ids);
2029 } else if (IsMediaContentOfType(content, MEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO)) {
2030 const VideoContentDescription* video =
2031 content->media_description()->as_video();
2032 MergeRtpHdrExts(video->rtp_header_extensions(), &offered_extensions.video,
2033 &all_regular_extensions, &all_encrypted_extensions,
2034 &used_ids);
2035 }
2036 }
2037
2038 // Add all encountered header extensions in the media description options that
2039 // are not in the current description.
2040
2041 for (const auto& entry : media_description_options) {
2042 RtpHeaderExtensions filtered_extensions =
2043 filtered_rtp_header_extensions(UnstoppedOrPresentRtpHeaderExtensions(
2044 entry.header_extensions, all_regular_extensions,
2045 all_encrypted_extensions));
2046 if (entry.type == MEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO)
2047 MergeRtpHdrExts(filtered_extensions, &offered_extensions.audio,
2048 &all_regular_extensions, &all_encrypted_extensions,
2049 &used_ids);
2050 else if (entry.type == MEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO)
2051 MergeRtpHdrExts(filtered_extensions, &offered_extensions.video,
2052 &all_regular_extensions, &all_encrypted_extensions,
2053 &used_ids);
2054 }
2055 // TODO(jbauch): Support adding encrypted header extensions to existing
2056 // sessions.
2057 if (enable_encrypted_rtp_header_extensions_ &&
2058 current_active_contents.empty()) {
2059 AddEncryptedVersionsOfHdrExts(&offered_extensions.audio,
2060 &all_encrypted_extensions, &used_ids);
2061 AddEncryptedVersionsOfHdrExts(&offered_extensions.video,
2062 &all_encrypted_extensions, &used_ids);
2063 }
2064 return offered_extensions;
2065}

2115// |audio_codecs| = set of all possible codecs that can be used, with correct
2116// payload type mappings
2117//
2118// |supported_audio_codecs| = set of codecs that are supported for the direction
2119// of this m= section
2120//
2121// acd->codecs() = set of previously negotiated codecs for this m= section
2122//
2123// The payload types should come from audio_codecs, but the order should come
2124// from acd->codecs() and then supported_codecs, to ensure that re-offers don't
2125// change existing codec priority, and that new codecs are added with the right
2126// priority.
2127bool MediaSessionDescriptionFactory::AddAudioContentForOffer(
2128 const MediaDescriptionOptions& media_description_options,
2129 const MediaSessionOptions& session_options,
2130 const ContentInfo* current_content,
2131 const SessionDescription* current_description,
2132 const RtpHeaderExtensions& audio_rtp_extensions,
2133 const AudioCodecs& audio_codecs,
2134 StreamParamsVec* current_streams,
2135 SessionDescription* desc,
2136 IceCredentialsIterator* ice_credentials) const {
2137 // Filter audio_codecs (which includes all codecs, with correctly remapped
2138 // payload types) based on transceiver direction.
2139 const AudioCodecs& supported_audio_codecs =
2140 GetAudioCodecsForOffer(media_description_options.direction);
2141
2142 AudioCodecs filtered_codecs;
2143
2144 if (!media_description_options.codec_preferences.empty()) {
2145 // Add the codecs from the current transceiver's codec preferences.
2146 // They override any existing codecs from previous negotiations.
2147 filtered_codecs = MatchCodecPreference(
2148 media_description_options.codec_preferences, supported_audio_codecs);
2149 } else {
2150 // Add the codecs from current content if it exists and is not rejected nor
2151 // recycled.
2152 if (current_content && !current_content->rejected &&
2153 current_content->name == media_description_options.mid) {
2154 RTC_CHECK(IsMediaContentOfType(current_content, MEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO));
2155 const AudioContentDescription* acd =
2156 current_content->media_description()->as_audio();
2157 for (const AudioCodec& codec : acd->codecs()) {
2158 if (FindMatchingCodec<AudioCodec>(acd->codecs(), audio_codecs, codec,
2159 nullptr)) {
2160 filtered_codecs.push_back(codec);
2161 }
2162 }
2163 }
2164 // Add other supported audio codecs.
2165 AudioCodec found_codec;
2166 for (const AudioCodec& codec : supported_audio_codecs) {
2167 if (FindMatchingCodec<AudioCodec>(supported_audio_codecs, audio_codecs,
2168 codec, &found_codec) &&
2169 !FindMatchingCodec<AudioCodec>(supported_audio_codecs,
2170 filtered_codecs, codec, nullptr)) {
2171 // Use the |found_codec| from |audio_codecs| because it has the
2172 // correctly mapped payload type.
2173 filtered_codecs.push_back(found_codec);
2174 }
2175 }
2176 }
2177 if (!session_options.vad_enabled) {
2178 // If application doesn't want CN codecs in offer.
2179 StripCNCodecs(&filtered_codecs);
2180 }
2181
2182 cricket::SecurePolicy sdes_policy =
2183 IsDtlsActive(current_content, current_description) ? cricket::SEC_DISABLED
2184 : secure();
2185
2186 auto audio = std::make_unique<AudioContentDescription>();
2187 std::vector<std::string> crypto_suites;
2188 GetSupportedAudioSdesCryptoSuiteNames(session_options.crypto_options,
2189 &crypto_suites);
2190 if (!CreateMediaContentOffer(media_description_options, session_options,
2191 filtered_codecs, sdes_policy,
2192 GetCryptos(current_content), crypto_suites,
2193 audio_rtp_extensions, ssrc_generator_,
2194 current_streams, audio.get())) {
2195 return false;
2196 }
2197
2198 bool secure_transport = (transport_desc_factory_->secure() != SEC_DISABLED);
2199 SetMediaProtocol(secure_transport, audio.get());
2200
2201 audio->set_direction(media_description_options.direction);
2202
2203 desc->AddContent(media_description_options.mid, MediaProtocolType::kRtp,
2204 media_description_options.stopped, std::move(audio));
2205 if (!AddTransportOffer(media_description_options.mid,
2206 media_description_options.transport_options,
2207 current_description, desc, ice_credentials)) {
2208 return false;
2209 }
2210
2211 return true;
2212}

2250 }

2308bool MediaSessionDescriptionFactory::AddDataContentForOffer(
2309 const MediaDescriptionOptions& media_description_options,
2310 const MediaSessionOptions& session_options,
2311 const ContentInfo* current_content,
2312 const SessionDescription* current_description,
2313 StreamParamsVec* current_streams,

2316 auto data = std::make_unique<SctpDataContentDescription>();
2317
2318 bool secure_transport = (transport_desc_factory_->secure() != SEC_DISABLED);
2319
2320 cricket::SecurePolicy sdes_policy =
2321 IsDtlsActive(current_content, current_description) ? cricket::SEC_DISABLED
2322 : secure();
2323 std::vector<std::string> crypto_suites;
2324 // SDES doesn't make sense for SCTP, so we disable it, and we only
2325 // get SDES crypto suites for RTP-based data channels.

2378// |audio_codecs| = set of all possible codecs that can be used, with correct
2379// payload type mappings
2380//
2381// |supported_audio_codecs| = set of codecs that are supported for the direction
2382// of this m= section
2383//
2384// acd->codecs() = set of previously negotiated codecs for this m= section
2385//
2386// The payload types should come from audio_codecs, but the order should come
2387// from acd->codecs() and then supported_codecs, to ensure that re-offers don't
2388// change existing codec priority, and that new codecs are added with the right
2389// priority.
2390bool MediaSessionDescriptionFactory::AddAudioContentForAnswer(
2391 const MediaDescriptionOptions& media_description_options,
2392 const MediaSessionOptions& session_options,
2393 const ContentInfo* offer_content,
2394 const SessionDescription* offer_description,
2395 const ContentInfo* current_content,
2396 const SessionDescription* current_description,
2397 const TransportInfo* bundle_transport,
2398 const AudioCodecs& audio_codecs,
2399 const RtpHeaderExtensions& default_audio_rtp_header_extensions,
2400 StreamParamsVec* current_streams,
2401 SessionDescription* answer,
2402 IceCredentialsIterator* ice_credentials) const {
2403 RTC_CHECK(IsMediaContentOfType(offer_content, MEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO));
2404 const AudioContentDescription* offer_audio_description =
2405 offer_content->media_description()->as_audio();
2406
2407 std::unique_ptr<TransportDescription> audio_transport = CreateTransportAnswer(
2408 media_description_options.mid, offer_description,
2409 media_description_options.transport_options, current_description,
2410 bundle_transport != nullptr, ice_credentials);
2411 if (!audio_transport) {
2412 return false;
2413 }
2414
2415 // Pick codecs based on the requested communications direction in the offer
2416 // and the selected direction in the answer.
2417 // Note these will be filtered one final time in CreateMediaContentAnswer.
2418 auto wants_rtd = media_description_options.direction;
2419 auto offer_rtd = offer_audio_description->direction();
2420 auto answer_rtd = NegotiateRtpTransceiverDirection(offer_rtd, wants_rtd);
2421 AudioCodecs supported_audio_codecs =
2422 GetAudioCodecsForAnswer(offer_rtd, answer_rtd);
2423
2424 AudioCodecs filtered_codecs;
2425
2426 if (!media_description_options.codec_preferences.empty()) {
2427 filtered_codecs = MatchCodecPreference(
2428 media_description_options.codec_preferences, supported_audio_codecs);
2429 } else {
2430 // Add the codecs from current content if it exists and is not rejected nor
2431 // recycled.
2432 if (current_content && !current_content->rejected &&
2433 current_content->name == media_description_options.mid) {
2434 RTC_CHECK(IsMediaContentOfType(current_content, MEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO));
2435 const AudioContentDescription* acd =
2436 current_content->media_description()->as_audio();
2437 for (const AudioCodec& codec : acd->codecs()) {
2438 if (FindMatchingCodec<AudioCodec>(acd->codecs(), audio_codecs, codec,
2439 nullptr)) {
2440 filtered_codecs.push_back(codec);
2441 }
2442 }
2443 }
2444 // Add other supported audio codecs.
2445 for (const AudioCodec& codec : supported_audio_codecs) {
2446 if (FindMatchingCodec<AudioCodec>(supported_audio_codecs, audio_codecs,
2447 codec, nullptr) &&
2448 !FindMatchingCodec<AudioCodec>(supported_audio_codecs,
2449 filtered_codecs, codec, nullptr)) {
2450 // We should use the local codec with local parameters and the codec id
2451 // would be correctly mapped in |NegotiateCodecs|.
2452 filtered_codecs.push_back(codec);
2453 }
2454 }
2455 }
2456 if (!session_options.vad_enabled) {
2457 // If application doesn't want CN codecs in answer.
2458 StripCNCodecs(&filtered_codecs);
2459 }
2460
2461 bool bundle_enabled = offer_description->HasGroup(GROUP_TYPE_BUNDLE) &&
2462 session_options.bundle_enabled;
2463 auto audio_answer = std::make_unique<AudioContentDescription>();
2464 // Do not require or create SDES cryptos if DTLS is used.
2465 cricket::SecurePolicy sdes_policy =
2466 audio_transport->secure() ? cricket::SEC_DISABLED : secure();
2467 if (!SetCodecsInAnswer(offer_audio_description, filtered_codecs,
2468 media_description_options, session_options,
2469 ssrc_generator_, current_streams,
2470 audio_answer.get())) {
2471 return false;
2472 }
2473 if (!CreateMediaContentAnswer(
2474 offer_audio_description, media_description_options, session_options,
2475 sdes_policy, GetCryptos(current_content),
2476 filtered_rtp_header_extensions(default_audio_rtp_header_extensions),
2477 ssrc_generator_, enable_encrypted_rtp_header_extensions_,
2478 current_streams, bundle_enabled, audio_answer.get())) {
2479 return false; // Fails the session setup.
2480 }
2481
2482 bool secure = bundle_transport ? bundle_transport->description.secure()
2483 : audio_transport->secure();
2484 bool rejected = media_description_options.stopped ||
2485 offer_content->rejected ||
2486 !IsMediaProtocolSupported(MEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO,
2487 audio_answer->protocol(), secure);
2488 if (!AddTransportAnswer(media_description_options.mid,
2489 *(audio_transport.get()), answer)) {
2490 return false;
2491 }
2492
2493 if (rejected) {
2494 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Audio m= section '" << media_description_options.mid
2495 << "' being rejected in answer.";
2496 }
2497
2498 answer->AddContent(media_description_options.mid, offer_content->type,
2499 rejected, std::move(audio_answer));
2500 return true;
2501}
