2503// TODO(kron): This function is very similar to AddAudioContentForAnswer.
2504// Refactor to reuse shared code.
2505bool MediaSessionDescriptionFactory::AddVideoContentForAnswer(
2506 const MediaDescriptionOptions& media_description_options,
2507 const MediaSessionOptions& session_options,
2508 const ContentInfo* offer_content,
2509 const SessionDescription* offer_description,
2510 const ContentInfo* current_content,
2511 const SessionDescription* current_description,
2512 const TransportInfo* bundle_transport,
2513 const VideoCodecs& video_codecs,
2514 const RtpHeaderExtensions& default_video_rtp_header_extensions,
2515 StreamParamsVec* current_streams,
2516 SessionDescription* answer,
2517 IceCredentialsIterator* ice_credentials) const {
2518 RTC_CHECK(IsMediaContentOfType(offer_content, MEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO));
2519 const VideoContentDescription* offer_video_description =
2520 offer_content->media_description()->as_video();
2521
2522 std::unique_ptr<TransportDescription> video_transport = CreateTransportAnswer(
2523 media_description_options.mid, offer_description,
2524 media_description_options.transport_options, current_description,
2525 bundle_transport != nullptr, ice_credentials);
2526 if (!video_transport) {
2527 return false;
2528 }
2529
2530 // Pick codecs based on the requested communications direction in the offer
2531 // and the selected direction in the answer.
2532 // Note these will be filtered one final time in CreateMediaContentAnswer.
2533 auto wants_rtd = media_description_options.direction;
2534 auto offer_rtd = offer_video_description->direction();
2535 auto answer_rtd = NegotiateRtpTransceiverDirection(offer_rtd, wants_rtd);
2536 VideoCodecs supported_video_codecs =
2537 GetVideoCodecsForAnswer(offer_rtd, answer_rtd);
2538
2539 VideoCodecs filtered_codecs;
2540
2541 if (!media_description_options.codec_preferences.empty()) {
2542 filtered_codecs = MatchCodecPreference(
2543 media_description_options.codec_preferences, supported_video_codecs);
2544 } else {
2545 // Add the codecs from current content if it exists and is not rejected nor
2546 // recycled.
2547 if (current_content && !current_content->rejected &&
2548 current_content->name == media_description_options.mid) {
2549 RTC_CHECK(IsMediaContentOfType(current_content, MEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO));
2550 const VideoContentDescription* vcd =
2551 current_content->media_description()->as_video();
2552 for (const VideoCodec& codec : vcd->codecs()) {
2553 if (FindMatchingCodec<VideoCodec>(vcd->codecs(), video_codecs, codec,
2554 nullptr)) {
2555 filtered_codecs.push_back(codec);
2556 }
2557 }
2558 }
2559 // Add other supported video codecs.
2560 for (const VideoCodec& codec : supported_video_codecs) {
2561 if (FindMatchingCodec<VideoCodec>(supported_video_codecs, video_codecs,
2562 codec, nullptr) &&
2563 !FindMatchingCodec<VideoCodec>(supported_video_codecs,
2564 filtered_codecs, codec, nullptr)) {
2565 // We should use the local codec with local parameters and the codec id
2566 // would be correctly mapped in |NegotiateCodecs|.
2567 filtered_codecs.push_back(codec);
2568 }
2569 }
2570 }
2571
2572 if (session_options.raw_packetization_for_video) {
2573 for (VideoCodec& codec : filtered_codecs) {
2574 if (codec.GetCodecType() == VideoCodec::CODEC_VIDEO) {
2575 codec.packetization = kPacketizationParamRaw;
2576 }
2577 }
2578 }
2579
2580 bool bundle_enabled = offer_description->HasGroup(GROUP_TYPE_BUNDLE) &&
2581 session_options.bundle_enabled;
2582 auto video_answer = std::make_unique<VideoContentDescription>();
2583 // Do not require or create SDES cryptos if DTLS is used.
2584 cricket::SecurePolicy sdes_policy =
2585 video_transport->secure() ? cricket::SEC_DISABLED : secure();
2586 if (!SetCodecsInAnswer(offer_video_description, filtered_codecs,
2587 media_description_options, session_options,
2588 ssrc_generator_, current_streams,
2589 video_answer.get())) {
2590 return false;
2591 }
2592 if (!CreateMediaContentAnswer(
2593 offer_video_description, media_description_options, session_options,
2594 sdes_policy, GetCryptos(current_content),
2595 filtered_rtp_header_extensions(default_video_rtp_header_extensions),
2596 ssrc_generator_, enable_encrypted_rtp_header_extensions_,
2597 current_streams, bundle_enabled, video_answer.get())) {
2598 return false; // Failed the sessin setup.
2599 }
2600 bool secure = bundle_transport ? bundle_transport->description.secure()
2601 : video_transport->secure();
2602 bool rejected = media_description_options.stopped ||
2603 offer_content->rejected ||
2604 !IsMediaProtocolSupported(MEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO,
2605 video_answer->protocol(), secure);
2606 if (!AddTransportAnswer(media_description_options.mid,
2607 *(video_transport.get()), answer)) {
2608 return false;
2609 }
2610
2611 if (!rejected) {
2612 video_answer->set_bandwidth(kAutoBandwidth);
2613 } else {
2614 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Video m= section '" << media_description_options.mid
2615 << "' being rejected in answer.";
2616 }
2617 answer->AddContent(media_description_options.mid, offer_content->type,
2618 rejected, std::move(video_answer));
2619 return true;
2620}

2622bool MediaSessionDescriptionFactory::AddDataContentForAnswer(
2623 const MediaDescriptionOptions& media_description_options,
2624 const MediaSessionOptions& session_options,
2625 const ContentInfo* offer_content,
2626 const SessionDescription* offer_description,
2627 const ContentInfo* current_content,
2628 const SessionDescription* current_description,
2629 const TransportInfo* bundle_transport,
2630 StreamParamsVec* current_streams,
2631 SessionDescription* answer,
2632 IceCredentialsIterator* ice_credentials) const {
2633 std::unique_ptr<TransportDescription> data_transport = CreateTransportAnswer(
2634 media_description_options.mid, offer_description,
2635 media_description_options.transport_options, current_description,
2636 bundle_transport != nullptr, ice_credentials);
2637 if (!data_transport) {
2638 return false;
2639 }
2640
2641 // Do not require or create SDES cryptos if DTLS is used.
2642 cricket::SecurePolicy sdes_policy =
2643 data_transport->secure() ? cricket::SEC_DISABLED : secure();
2644 bool bundle_enabled = offer_description->HasGroup(GROUP_TYPE_BUNDLE) &&
2645 session_options.bundle_enabled;
2646 RTC_CHECK(IsMediaContentOfType(offer_content, MEDIA_TYPE_DATA));
2647 std::unique_ptr<MediaContentDescription> data_answer;
2648 if (offer_content->media_description()->as_sctp()) {
2649 // SCTP data content
2650 data_answer = std::make_unique<SctpDataContentDescription>();
2651 const SctpDataContentDescription* offer_data_description =
2652 offer_content->media_description()->as_sctp();
2653 // Respond with the offerer's proto, whatever it is.
2654 data_answer->as_sctp()->set_protocol(offer_data_description->protocol());
2655 // Respond with our max message size or the remote max messsage size,
2656 // whichever is smaller.
2657 // 0 is treated specially - it means "I can accept any size". Since
2658 // we do not implement infinite size messages, reply with
2659 // kSctpSendBufferSize.
2660 if (offer_data_description->max_message_size() == 0) {
2661 data_answer->as_sctp()->set_max_message_size(kSctpSendBufferSize);
2662 } else {
2663 data_answer->as_sctp()->set_max_message_size(std::min(
2664 offer_data_description->max_message_size(), kSctpSendBufferSize));
2665 }
2666 if (!CreateMediaContentAnswer(
2667 offer_data_description, media_description_options, session_options,
2668 sdes_policy, GetCryptos(current_content), RtpHeaderExtensions(),
2669 ssrc_generator_, enable_encrypted_rtp_header_extensions_,
2670 current_streams, bundle_enabled, data_answer.get())) {
2671 return false; // Fails the session setup.
2672 }
2673 // Respond with sctpmap if the offer uses sctpmap.
2674 bool offer_uses_sctpmap = offer_data_description->use_sctpmap();
2675 data_answer->as_sctp()->set_use_sctpmap(offer_uses_sctpmap);
2676 } else {
2677 RTC_NOTREACHED() << "Non-SCTP data content found";
2678 }
2679
2680 bool secure = bundle_transport ? bundle_transport->description.secure()
2681 : data_transport->secure();
2682
2683 bool rejected = media_description_options.stopped ||
2684 offer_content->rejected ||
2685 !IsMediaProtocolSupported(MEDIA_TYPE_DATA,
2686 data_answer->protocol(), secure);
2687 if (!AddTransportAnswer(media_description_options.mid,
2688 *(data_transport.get()), answer)) {
2689 return false;
2690 }
2691
2692 answer->AddContent(media_description_options.mid, offer_content->type,
2693 rejected, std::move(data_answer));
2694 return true;
2695}

2697bool MediaSessionDescriptionFactory::AddUnsupportedContentForAnswer(
2698 const MediaDescriptionOptions& media_description_options,
2699 const MediaSessionOptions& session_options,
2700 const ContentInfo* offer_content,
2701 const SessionDescription* offer_description,
2702 const ContentInfo* current_content,
2703 const SessionDescription* current_description,
2704 const TransportInfo* bundle_transport,
2705 SessionDescription* answer,
2706 IceCredentialsIterator* ice_credentials) const {
2707 std::unique_ptr<TransportDescription> unsupported_transport =
2708 CreateTransportAnswer(media_description_options.mid, offer_description,
2709 media_description_options.transport_options,
2710 current_description, bundle_transport != nullptr,
2711 ice_credentials);
2712 if (!unsupported_transport) {
2713 return false;
2714 }
2715 RTC_CHECK(IsMediaContentOfType(offer_content, MEDIA_TYPE_UNSUPPORTED));
2716
2717 const UnsupportedContentDescription* offer_unsupported_description =
2718 offer_content->media_description()->as_unsupported();
2719 std::unique_ptr<MediaContentDescription> unsupported_answer =
2720 std::make_unique<UnsupportedContentDescription>(
2721 offer_unsupported_description->media_type());
2722 unsupported_answer->set_protocol(offer_unsupported_description->protocol());
2723
2724 if (!AddTransportAnswer(media_description_options.mid,
2725 *(unsupported_transport.get()), answer)) {
2726 return false;
2727 }
2728 answer->AddContent(media_description_options.mid, offer_content->type,
2729 /*rejected=*/true, std::move(unsupported_answer));
2730 return true;
2731}

2733void MediaSessionDescriptionFactory::ComputeAudioCodecsIntersectionAndUnion() {
2734 audio_sendrecv_codecs_.clear();
2735 all_audio_codecs_.clear();
2736 // Compute the audio codecs union.
2737 for (const AudioCodec& send : audio_send_codecs_) {
2738 all_audio_codecs_.push_back(send);
2739 if (!FindMatchingCodec<AudioCodec>(audio_send_codecs_, audio_recv_codecs_,
2740 send, nullptr)) {
2741 // It doesn't make sense to have an RTX codec we support sending but not
2742 // receiving.
2743 RTC_DCHECK(!IsRtxCodec(send));
2744 }
2745 }
2746 for (const AudioCodec& recv : audio_recv_codecs_) {
2747 if (!FindMatchingCodec<AudioCodec>(audio_recv_codecs_, audio_send_codecs_,
2748 recv, nullptr)) {
2749 all_audio_codecs_.push_back(recv);
2750 }
2751 }
2752 // Use NegotiateCodecs to merge our codec lists, since the operation is
2753 // essentially the same. Put send_codecs as the offered_codecs, which is the
2754 // order we'd like to follow. The reasoning is that encoding is usually more
2755 // expensive than decoding, and prioritizing a codec in the send list probably
2756 // means it's a codec we can handle efficiently.
2757 NegotiateCodecs(audio_recv_codecs_, audio_send_codecs_,
2758 &audio_sendrecv_codecs_, true);
2759}
2760
2761void MediaSessionDescriptionFactory::ComputeVideoCodecsIntersectionAndUnion() {
2762 video_sendrecv_codecs_.clear();
2763 all_video_codecs_.clear();
2764 // Compute the video codecs union.
2765 for (const VideoCodec& send : video_send_codecs_) {
2766 all_video_codecs_.push_back(send);
2767 if (!FindMatchingCodec<VideoCodec>(video_send_codecs_, video_recv_codecs_,
2768 send, nullptr)) {
2769 // TODO(kron): This check is violated by the unit test:
2770 // MediaSessionDescriptionFactoryTest.RtxWithoutApt
2771 // Remove either the test or the check.
2772
2773 // It doesn't make sense to have an RTX codec we support sending but not
2774 // receiving.
2775 // RTC_DCHECK(!IsRtxCodec(send));
2776 }
2777 }
2778 for (const VideoCodec& recv : video_recv_codecs_) {
2779 if (!FindMatchingCodec<VideoCodec>(video_recv_codecs_, video_send_codecs_,
2780 recv, nullptr)) {
2781 all_video_codecs_.push_back(recv);
2782 }
2783 }
2784 // Use NegotiateCodecs to merge our codec lists, since the operation is
2785 // essentially the same. Put send_codecs as the offered_codecs, which is the
2786 // order we'd like to follow. The reasoning is that encoding is usually more
2787 // expensive than decoding, and prioritizing a codec in the send list probably
2788 // means it's a codec we can handle efficiently.
2789 NegotiateCodecs(video_recv_codecs_, video_send_codecs_,
2790 &video_sendrecv_codecs_, true);
2791}
